ce/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France fed off the home crowd\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s energy and punched Canada in the mouth right from the opening tip.\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 358, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 258, \"end\": 264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9801858565735146, \"rank\": 0.020205399106271314, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 311, \"end\": 317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9991427580404559, \"rank\": 0.000787536822249935, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Isaia Cordinier knocked down back-to-back triples and scored 10 straight points for the French to fuel a 19-5 advantage as the Canadians missed 10 of their 12 field goal attempts and committed seven turnovers in the first quarter.\", \"from\": 359, \"to\": 589, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 359, \"end\": 374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isa\\u00efa_Cordinier\", \"score\": 0.999999923104045, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Isaia Cordinier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isa\\u00efa_Cordinier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isa\\u00efa_Cordinier\"}, {\"begin\": 447, \"end\": 453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8710452754906512, \"rank\": 0.1338106208240765, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The squad that had rolled through Group A unscathed was all of a sudden in a fight for its life through the first 10 minutes of play in the quarterfinal round.\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Shai Gilgeous-Alexander started to change Canada\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s outlook in the second quarter.\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 834, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 751, \"end\": 774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shai_Gilgeous-Alexander\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shai Gilgeous-Alexander\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shai_Gilgeous-Alexander\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shai_Gilgeous-Alexander\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After a quiet opening from the All-NBA guard, Gilgeous-Alexander got into a rhythm with three straight midrange jumpers, followed by a stepback 3-pointer that cut the deficit to single-digits with under four minutes left in the first half.\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 1074, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Oklahoma City Thunder superstar scored 11 straight points for the Canadians while France\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s touted frontcourt watched from the bench.\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1079, \"end\": 1087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma_Sooners_men's_basketball\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.562057876952122e-15, \"text\": \"Oklahoma\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma_Sooners_men's_basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma_Sooners_men's_basketball\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Victor Wembanyama had his fingerprints all over the game from the start, Rudy Gobert had to wait until the second quarter to see his first action, as the reigning NBA Defensive Player of the Year came off the bench for France for the first time in Olympic competition.\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1489, \"entities\": 